EstablishmentDetail.RightToReply:
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	I agree with the inspection findings but have since carried out the following improvements: -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	a. A new management system has been implemented.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	b. The staff have been trained/re-trained/given instruction/are under revised supervisory arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:18.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	The conditions found at the time of the inspection were not typical of the normal conditions maintained at the establishment and arose because we had a system in place, for whatever reason labelling of goods going into freezer and coming out were not done. As we couldn&amp;rsquo;t prove that these goods were frozen before their use by dates (although can prove when purchased) they had to be classed as out of date stock.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:18.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	We have now implemented a new structure within our business to ensure this never happens and that all procedures are followed no matter or how busy we may be. We are now working closely with the EHO to get another visit to show what has been done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:18.0pt;&quot;&gt;
	Although the EHO could see that a system of labelling had previously been in place with regards to freezing items before the use by date, he still had to record these and we disposed of them.&lt;/p&gt;
